 SHO Madjozi is living proof that dreams do come true when
you work hard. After she penned a song dedicated to the wrestling
superstar, John Cena, the Limpopo-born star finally got to meet the man in
person. This happened in the early hours of today. She was a guest
at the Kelly Clarkson Show, a talk show hosted by award-winning Kelly Clarkson. While performing the song, John Cena appeared from behind
and danced next to Sho Madjozi’s song. And she couldn’t hide her excitement
when she saw him. She was on the show talking about her musical journey. The award-winning star first performed the song, Sho
Madjozi. John Cena reacted to the song and became an instant hit.  